{
  "texts": [
    "Other than early stage uses such as brainstorming or outlining, researchers most commonly reported using generative AI towards the end of their research process to revise written outputs.",
    "28 For instance, a researcher in earth sciences explained how they use generative AI to revise an article draft:",
    "I'll write material, and then usually I'll only ever feed it a paragraph at a time or a section at a time, and I'll ask it to make it more readable.",
    "You'll prompt it and tell it who the audience is.",
    "So, you'd say, \"this is for an audience of farmers or agricultural researchers\" and then \"make this paragraph more readable at a [grade] level."
  ]
}